<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p><strong>Bus routes:</strong> <br/>160, 229, 269, 286, B14, R11</p><br/><p><strong>Trains: </strong><br/>Trains travel regularly to Sidcup  station from  London Charing Cross, London Bridge, Waterloo East, Cannon  Street and  New Cross as well as Dartford, Gravesend, Slade Green and  Crayford. The  hospital is about 25 minutes walk from Sidcup station or  you can take a  bus or taxi – buses 160, 229 and 286 run between the hospital  grounds  and the train station.</p><br/><p><strong>Parking: <br/></strong>Queen  Mary’s  Hospital has 350 pay and display public parking spaces with bays for  people with  disabilities outside each main building. There is a paved area to the rear of Java coffee shop for motorcycles (C  Block). Cycle racks are also near Java coffee shop.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There is limited pay and display car parking on the hospital site.</p>
